  <walkingDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Walking in Belle Plagne</strong></p>
<p>There is easy access to the open countryside from the Chalet Hotel des Deux Domaines by foot or by the Roche de Mio cable-car with a range of hiking trails to suit everybody. All the paths are well signposted and you will discover lakes and streams and tremendous vistas including views over to Europe's highest peak Mont Blanc. You can also plan your walk to return via one of the La Plagne villages and the free bus service back. Included are 2 half day guided walks which are led by English speaking local guides or your Inghams Rep. These will be pleasant strolls on well marked paths with uphill and downhill sections.</p>
<p><strong>Walking in Belle Plagne</strong></p>
<p>There is easy access to the open countryside from the Chalet Hotel des Deux Domaines by foot or by the Roche de Mio cable-car with a range of hiking trails to suit everybody. All the paths are well signposted and you will discover lakes and streams and tremendous vistas including views over to Europe's highest peak Mont Blanc. You can also plan your walk to return via one of the La Plagne villages and the free bus service back. Included are 2 half day guided walks which are led by English speaking local guides or your Inghams Rep. These will be pleasant strolls on well marked paths with uphill and downhill sections.</p>
<p>On Thursday is the<strong> Beaufort Dairy Farm Walk</strong> which includes a visit to the farm to see how the milk and cheese are produced. On Sunday is the botanical walk called '<strong>In Search of the Edelweiss</strong>' looking for the best views and the best flora and fauna of the area. These walks are a great way to explore the local area and get to know your fellow guests.&lt;/p</p>]]></walkingDescription>
